<p>LandWarNet enables warfighting and generating force functions by providing a manageable, interoperable, integrated, network enterprise from Post / Camp / Station to the tactical edge that connects all of our forces, systems, platforms, and installations into a collaborative environment.</p>
<p class="BubbleTitleSection">What is LandWarNet?</p>
<p>LandWarNet is the Army's enterprise network -- a secure, standards-based, versatile infrastructure linked by networked, redundant transport systems, sensors, warfighting and business applications to provide our Soldiers, civilians and unified action partners the information they need, when they need it, in any environment. It provides connectivity to both classified and unclassified networks at post/camp/station, at home, when deployed, TDY, or in austere locations. LandWarNet is also part of the Department of Defense Information Network (DoDIN); interconnected to the overarching joint information environment that includes networks and services for each military service, federal agencies, in the Department of Defense. (See Figure 1)</p>
